.SH NAME
\*LSgColorChooserSetCurrentColor \*O\(em A ColorChooser function that sets the selected color of the ColorChooser without changing the stored color
.iX "SgColorChooserSetCurrentColor"
.iX "ColorChooser functions" "SgColorChooserSetCurrentColor"
.SH SYNOPSIS
.sS
.iS
\&#include <Sgm/ColorC.h>
.sp \n(PDu
void SgColorChooserSetCurrentColor (\*Vwidget, red, green, blue\*L)
.ta .5i 1.7i
	Widget	\*Vwidget\*L;
	short	\*Vred\*L;
	short	\*Vgreen\*L;
	short	\*Vblue\*L;
.wH .fi
.ne 10
.iE
.sE
.SH DESCRIPTION
\*LSgColorChooserSetCurrentColor\*O sets the currents selected color of the 
given ColorChooser widget. This means that all the components of the 
ColorChooser, the color 
hexagon, color sliders, color swatches, and color value text widgets will all
reflect the new color. The given color must be in RGB color space.

The difference between SgColorChooserSetCurrentColor and 
SgColorChooserSetColor is that SgColorChooserSetCurrentColor does not
alter the value of the Stored Color color swatch.
.VL .75i 
.LI "\*Vwidget\*O"
Specifies the ColorChooser widget ID.
.LI "\*Vred\*O"
Specifies the red color component in an RGB color space.
.LI "\*Vgreen\*O"
Specifies the green color component in an RGB color space.
.LI "\*Vblue\*O"
Specifies the blue color component in an RGB color space.
.LE 
.PP 
For a complete definition of ColorChooser widget and its associated 
resources, see
\*LSgColorChooser(3X)\*O.
